WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.000
Dominoes, Quick Starter, Lisa's Song by Leslie Thompson.

00:06.000 --> 00:10.880
Read by Richard Linson, Chris Mills, Penny Rawlins,

00:10.880 --> 00:16.280
Jane Whittenshaw, James Daniel Wilson, and Jennifer Woodwood.

00:16.280 --> 00:21.960
Published in copyright, Oxford University Press 2012.

00:21.960 --> 00:25.400
Chapter 1, Al's First Love.

00:25.400 --> 00:35.400
MUSIC

00:35.400 --> 00:38.840
Al Brown is 13.

00:38.840 --> 00:44.000
He lives with his parents in a little house.

00:44.000 --> 00:48.000
It's in Nottingham in England.

00:48.000 --> 00:54.600
The family are happy, but they have not got much money.

00:54.600 --> 00:58.760
So life is not easy.

00:58.760 --> 01:06.400
When our story begins, Mrs. Brown is expecting a baby.

01:06.400 --> 01:13.440
Al is waiting excitedly for his new little brother or sister.

01:13.440 --> 01:17.680
Al's first love is music.

01:17.680 --> 01:22.840
He can play the guitar very well.

01:22.840 --> 01:29.800
He is in a band, fast cars, with three of his friends.

01:29.800 --> 01:36.000
They are Emma, Mick, and Ben.

01:36.000 --> 01:41.280
Ben and Al play the guitars in the band.

01:41.280 --> 01:49.320
Emma sings, and Mick plays the drums.

01:49.760 --> 01:53.720
Al writes songs for the band.

01:53.720 --> 01:57.360
They play at Ben's house.

01:57.360 --> 02:02.880
Al's parents often come and listen to them.

02:02.880 --> 02:07.600
They are good friends with Ben's parents.

02:07.600 --> 02:11.680
Our boy can't live without his music.

02:11.680 --> 02:14.520
Al's parents tell everyone.

02:14.520 --> 02:26.520
MUSIC

02:26.520 --> 02:28.520
Chapter 2.

02:28.520 --> 02:30.520
Al's Baby Sister.

02:30.520 --> 02:40.520
MUSIC

02:40.520 --> 02:46.920
One morning, Mrs. Brown does not feel well.

02:46.920 --> 02:51.320
The baby's coming, she says.

02:51.320 --> 02:54.520
What, it's six weeks early.

02:54.520 --> 02:57.120
Mr. Brown cries.

02:57.120 --> 02:59.920
Yes, I know.

02:59.920 --> 03:03.520
But please, take me to the hospital.

03:03.520 --> 03:07.120
This baby can't wait.

03:07.120 --> 03:10.720
Mrs. Brown is right.

03:10.720 --> 03:16.440
After six hours, Lisa arrives.

03:16.440 --> 03:22.000
She is beautiful, but she is very little.

03:22.000 --> 03:28.520
She must stay in hospital for two weeks.

03:28.520 --> 03:34.320
When Lisa comes home, life is not the same.

03:34.400 --> 03:40.760
The baby cries a lot, and she doesn't eat much.

03:40.760 --> 03:45.640
Is the little girl all right?

03:45.640 --> 03:49.040
Everyone is tired.

03:49.040 --> 03:54.680
When Al tries to play his guitar, his mother says,

03:54.680 --> 03:58.720
Shh, Lisa's sleeping.

03:58.720 --> 04:01.000
Mr. Brown says,

04:01.000 --> 04:04.600
You must help more in the house, Al.

04:04.600 --> 04:07.800
Your mother's very tired.

04:07.800 --> 04:13.400
Al tries to help, but he is tired too.

04:13.400 --> 04:22.600
He can't concentrate at school, and he forgets to do his homework.

04:22.600 --> 04:29.200
One day, Al visits his grandfather, Jack Brown.

04:29.200 --> 04:32.800
The old man lives alone.

04:32.800 --> 04:35.000
Al says.

04:35.000 --> 04:38.600
Mum and Dad never listen to me now.

04:38.600 --> 04:42.400
They're always with Lisa.

04:42.400 --> 04:47.000
A new baby is a lot of work.

04:47.000 --> 04:53.000
Jack says, You must understand that, Al.

04:53.000 --> 04:55.600
But what about you?

04:55.600 --> 04:58.800
Are you writing any new songs?

04:58.800 --> 05:02.600
You're a good songwriter.

05:02.600 --> 05:06.600
Al says nothing to his grandfather.

05:06.600 --> 05:12.400
He has no time for the band these days.

05:12.400 --> 05:18.800
When Jack is alone, he takes out an old photograph.

05:18.800 --> 05:21.200
He looks at it.

05:21.200 --> 05:26.800
It is a picture of his sister, Alice.

05:27.000 --> 05:30.400
Life's short, Al.

05:30.400 --> 05:32.600
He says quietly.

05:32.600 --> 05:36.000
Be good to your sister.

05:36.000 --> 05:42.000
You're older, but you don't always know best.

05:42.000 --> 05:56.000
CHAPTER 3

05:56.000 --> 06:08.000
AL'S ANGRY FRIENDS

06:08.000 --> 06:14.000
Al's friends are waiting for him at Ben's house.

06:14.000 --> 06:18.000
Al is late again.

06:18.000 --> 06:20.000
Where is he?

06:20.000 --> 06:22.000
Emma asks.

06:22.000 --> 06:26.000
We can't begin playing without him.

06:26.000 --> 06:29.000
He's always late these days.

06:29.000 --> 06:32.000
Ben says angrily.

06:32.000 --> 06:35.000
And he can't concentrate.

06:35.000 --> 06:39.000
Let's look for a different guitar player.

06:39.000 --> 06:42.000
My brother wants to be in the band.

06:42.000 --> 06:45.000
You're right, says Mick.

06:45.000 --> 06:48.000
Let's find someone new.

06:48.000 --> 06:53.000
Emma does not want to lose Al.

06:53.000 --> 06:57.000
She calls him on her mobile phone.

06:57.000 --> 07:00.000
Where are you?

07:00.000 --> 07:02.000
We're waiting for you.

07:02.000 --> 07:06.000
Get here fast and say sorry.

07:06.000 --> 07:11.000
Then perhaps we can forget these last weeks.

07:11.000 --> 07:14.000
But you must change, Al.

07:14.000 --> 07:19.000
You must give more time to the band.

07:19.000 --> 07:24.000
Al is in an internet cafe.

07:24.000 --> 07:28.000
He is trying to do his homework.

07:28.000 --> 07:33.000
Emma, things aren't easy for me these days.

07:33.000 --> 07:36.000
I can't work at home.

07:36.000 --> 07:39.000
Lisa's always crying.

07:39.000 --> 07:43.000
My parents are always with her.

07:43.000 --> 07:46.000
They tell me, do this.

07:46.000 --> 07:48.000
Do that.

07:48.000 --> 07:51.000
Now you're doing the same.

07:51.000 --> 07:54.000
Leave me alone.

07:54.000 --> 08:00.000
And he stops the call and puts the phone down.

08:00.000 --> 08:04.000
Emma is very angry.

08:04.000 --> 08:09.000
I'm trying to help Al, but he's not interested.

08:09.000 --> 08:11.000
She thinks.

08:11.000 --> 08:15.000
She quickly sends him a phone message.

08:15.000 --> 08:20.000
Fast cars is looking for a new guitar player.

08:21.000 --> 08:24.000
Don't worry about us.

08:24.000 --> 08:27.000
We don't need you anymore, Al.

08:27.000 --> 08:30.000
Goodbye.

08:30.000 --> 08:36.000
Al tries to phone Emma, but she doesn't answer.

08:36.000 --> 08:38.000
How does he feel?

08:38.000 --> 08:40.000
Bad.

08:40.000 --> 08:44.000
He does not want to lose his friends.

08:44.000 --> 08:48.000
And he loves playing in the band.

08:48.000 --> 08:51.000
But what can he do now?

08:51.000 --> 08:56.000
Just then, his phone rings again.

08:56.000 --> 08:59.000
This time, it's his grandfather.

08:59.000 --> 09:13.000
Chapter 4.

09:13.000 --> 09:17.000
Something is wrong.

09:17.000 --> 09:35.000
Al does not answer his mobile, and his grandfather does not leave a message for him.

09:35.000 --> 09:38.000
I can phone him later.

09:38.000 --> 09:41.000
Al thinks.

09:41.000 --> 09:46.000
When Al goes home, something is wrong.

09:46.000 --> 09:54.000
His mother's eyes are red, and his father's face is white.

09:54.000 --> 09:56.000
What's the matter?

09:56.000 --> 09:58.000
Al asks.

09:58.000 --> 10:00.000
It's your sister.

10:00.000 --> 10:02.000
Dad says.

10:02.000 --> 10:04.000
She's ill.

10:04.000 --> 10:06.000
Ill?

10:06.000 --> 10:09.000
Her heart isn't right, Al.

10:09.000 --> 10:13.000
She needs an operation, and quickly.

10:14.000 --> 10:16.000
There's more.

10:16.000 --> 10:19.000
It's a difficult operation.

10:19.000 --> 10:22.000
No hospital in England can do it.

10:22.000 --> 10:27.000
Lisa needs to go to the United States for it.

10:27.000 --> 10:29.000
I see.

10:29.000 --> 10:32.000
So, when are you going?

10:32.000 --> 10:34.000
We don't know.

10:34.000 --> 10:37.000
The operation's expensive.

10:37.000 --> 10:42.000
And there are the plane tickets and the hotel, too?

10:42.000 --> 10:45.000
Mr. Brown tries to smile.

10:45.000 --> 10:47.000
But we can find the money.

10:47.000 --> 10:50.000
Don't worry about it.

10:50.000 --> 10:55.000
Now Al is very sad and alone.

10:55.000 --> 10:59.000
Lisa is very ill, he knows.

10:59.000 --> 11:03.000
Perhaps he can phone Emma.

11:03.000 --> 11:11.000
Then, on his mobile, he sees a message from his grandfather.

11:11.000 --> 11:14.000
Come and see me.

11:14.000 --> 11:18.000
I know about Lisa.

11:18.000 --> 11:22.000
Jack is waiting for Al.

11:22.000 --> 11:29.000
He is thinking about his sister, Alice, dead at 13.

11:29.000 --> 11:33.000
Suddenly, Al runs in.

11:33.000 --> 11:37.000
Granddad, what can we do?

11:37.000 --> 11:42.000
Where can we find the money for Lisa's operation?

11:42.000 --> 11:45.000
Take it easy, Al.

11:45.000 --> 11:47.000
Says Granddad.

11:47.000 --> 11:50.000
I've got an idea.

11:50.000 --> 11:58.000
Tell your friends in the band, write a song for Lisa.

11:58.000 --> 12:01.000
A song for Lisa?

12:01.000 --> 12:03.000
How can that help?

12:03.000 --> 12:06.000
Trust me, Al.

12:06.000 --> 12:08.000
It can.

12:08.000 --> 12:13.000
Go home now and write your song.

12:34.000 --> 12:43.000
Back home, Al talks to his parents.

12:43.000 --> 12:46.000
I want to write a song for Lisa.

12:46.000 --> 12:50.000
I want to tell everyone about her.

12:50.000 --> 12:53.000
Mr. and Mrs. Brown smile.

12:53.000 --> 12:56.000
What a nice idea.

12:56.000 --> 12:58.000
His mum says.

12:58.000 --> 13:01.000
Thanks, Al.

13:01.000 --> 13:04.000
Al phones his friends.

13:04.000 --> 13:07.000
He meets them at Ben's house.

13:07.000 --> 13:10.000
He says sorry.

13:10.000 --> 13:16.000
Then, he tells them all about Lisa and the song.

13:16.000 --> 13:21.000
Emma looks at Mick and Ben.

13:21.000 --> 13:24.000
What do you think, boys?

13:24.000 --> 13:27.000
Can Al come back to the band now?

13:27.000 --> 13:29.000
She asks.

13:29.000 --> 13:31.000
Yes.

13:31.000 --> 13:33.000
Ben laughs.

13:33.000 --> 13:35.000
We need him.

13:35.000 --> 13:39.000
My brother can't play the guitar at all.

13:39.000 --> 13:42.000
And he can't write songs.

13:42.000 --> 13:44.000
Mick says.

13:44.000 --> 13:46.000
I've got an idea.

13:46.000 --> 13:48.000
Emma says.

13:48.000 --> 13:53.000
We can play Al's new song at our gig.

13:53.000 --> 13:55.000
What gig?

13:56.000 --> 13:58.000
The gig for Lisa.

13:58.000 --> 14:00.000
Emma says.

14:00.000 --> 14:03.000
People can pay at the door.

14:03.000 --> 14:07.000
With their help, Lisa can have her operation.

14:07.000 --> 14:09.000
Good idea.

14:09.000 --> 14:12.000
Ben cries excitedly.

14:12.000 --> 14:17.000
Let's tell people about it on our website.

14:17.000 --> 14:23.000
So Mick puts the day and time of their next gig

14:23.000 --> 14:27.000
up on the band's website.

14:27.000 --> 14:32.000
Two weeks later, after lots of work,

14:32.000 --> 14:36.000
the band plays at Al's school.

14:36.000 --> 14:40.000
Al's family and friends are there.

14:40.000 --> 14:43.000
Late in the evening,

14:43.000 --> 14:47.000
Al sings Lisa's song.

14:47.000 --> 14:51.000
Some people from the radio are there too.

14:51.000 --> 14:53.000
They record the song.

15:02.000 --> 15:05.000
Let's sing for Lisa and her life.

15:05.000 --> 15:07.000
The future's in her eyes are blue.

15:07.000 --> 15:10.000
A bright tomorrow's endless smile.

15:10.000 --> 15:14.000
So let's all help those times come true.

15:22.000 --> 15:27.000
Next day, Al and his friends

15:27.000 --> 15:31.000
look at the money from the gig.

15:31.000 --> 15:34.000
How much is there?

15:34.000 --> 15:38.000
Can Lisa have her operation now?

15:38.000 --> 15:52.000
Chapter 6

15:52.000 --> 15:54.000
Past concerts.

15:54.000 --> 15:56.000
Future gigs.

15:56.000 --> 16:06.000
We need more money.

16:06.000 --> 16:09.000
Al says.

16:09.000 --> 16:14.000
Then let's put Lisa's song on our website.

16:14.000 --> 16:16.000
Ben cries.

16:16.000 --> 16:20.000
People can pay for it and download it.

16:20.000 --> 16:25.000
People hear about Lisa's song on the radio.

16:25.000 --> 16:30.000
They pay and download it from the website.

16:30.000 --> 16:37.000
Soon, Al's family have the money for America.

16:37.000 --> 16:39.000
At the airport,

16:39.000 --> 16:44.000
Al and his grandfather say goodbye.

16:44.000 --> 16:47.000
Good luck!

16:47.000 --> 16:52.000
Al calls to his parents and Lisa.

16:52.000 --> 16:59.000
Suddenly, Jack remembers a night in 1941.

16:59.000 --> 17:02.000
His mother is dead.

17:02.000 --> 17:06.000
His father is away at the war.

17:06.000 --> 17:10.000
He is the man of the house now.

17:10.000 --> 17:12.000
Night after night,

17:12.000 --> 17:17.000
planes drop their bombs on their town.

17:17.000 --> 17:20.000
People are afraid.

17:20.000 --> 17:28.000
His sister, Alice, wants to sing and dance and forget the war.

17:28.000 --> 17:33.000
He hears her words that night and his answer.

17:33.000 --> 17:36.000
Please, can I go out, Jack?

17:36.000 --> 17:39.000
I want to sing at the concert.

17:39.000 --> 17:42.000
My friends are waiting.

17:42.000 --> 17:44.000
No, Alice.

17:44.000 --> 17:47.000
You're 13.

17:47.000 --> 17:50.000
You must stay at home.

17:50.000 --> 17:55.000
Later, he is working at the hospital.

17:55.000 --> 17:57.000
Bombs are dropping.

17:57.000 --> 18:00.000
The sky is red.

18:00.000 --> 18:03.000
Then someone says,

18:03.000 --> 18:07.000
Jack, there's a bomb in your street.

18:07.000 --> 18:10.000
Your house is on fire.

18:10.000 --> 18:12.000
Alice?

18:12.000 --> 18:14.000
He cries.

18:14.000 --> 18:17.000
He runs home.

18:17.000 --> 18:20.000
But he can do nothing.

18:20.000 --> 18:25.000
He never sees Alice again.

18:25.000 --> 18:28.000
What's the matter, Grandad?

18:28.000 --> 18:31.000
Al asks.

18:31.000 --> 18:34.000
Jack smiles at his grandson.

18:34.000 --> 18:39.000
He sees a lot of Alice in the boy.

18:39.000 --> 18:44.000
Sometimes, past experience teaches you things.

18:44.000 --> 18:50.000
Oh, it's not important now.

18:50.000 --> 18:55.000
But you must write some more songs.

18:55.000 --> 18:58.000
When's the band's next concert?

18:58.000 --> 19:01.000
Er, gig.

19:01.000 --> 19:03.000
Soon, Grandad.

19:03.000 --> 19:05.000
With that,

19:05.000 --> 19:08.000
Grandfather and grandson,

19:08.000 --> 19:11.000
leave the airport and go home.

